     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="12"/>
   <head>TO Mrs. <hi>Alice Sutcliffe,</hi> on her divine Medita<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tions.</head>
   <l>WHen I had read</l>
   <l>your holy <hi>Meditatiōs,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>And in them view'd</l>
   <l>th' <hi>uncertainty</hi> of <hi>Life,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>The <hi>motives,</hi> and true <hi>Spurres</hi>
   </l>
   <l>to all good <hi>Nations.</hi>
   </l>
   <l>The <hi>Peace</hi> of <hi>Conscience,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>and the <hi>Godly</hi>'s strife,</l>
   <l>The <hi>Danger</hi> of <hi>delaying</hi>
   </l>
   <l>to <hi>Repent,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>And the <hi>deceipt</hi> of <hi>pleasures,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>by <hi>Consent.</hi>
   </l>
   <pb facs="12"/>
   <l>The <hi>cōfort</hi> of weake <hi>Christiās,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>with their <hi>warning,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>From fearefull <hi>back-slides;</hi>
   </l>
   <l>And the debt we' are in,</l>
   <l>To follow <hi>Goodnesse,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>by our owne discerning</l>
   <l>Our great <hi>reward,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>th' <hi>aeternall Crown</hi> to win.</l>
   <l>I sayd, who' had supp'd so deepe</l>
   <l>of this sweet <hi>Chalice,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Must <hi>CELIA</hi> bee,</l>
   <l>the <hi>Anagram</hi> of <hi>ALICE.</hi>
   </l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Ben. Ionson.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
